        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
          "email": "jay@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2011-04-26 00:11:58.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-118 clear_inode: BUG_ON(inode->i_data.nrpages)",
        "message": "LU-118 clear_inode: BUG_ON(inode->i_data.nrpages)\n\nThis patch does a lot of fixes and cleanup:\n - grab an inode refcount by top cl_object, so that it can't go away\n - cl_object now can be purged by shrinker\n - change the way to create cl_object, now it will be created in\n   ll_file_open, ll_setattr_ost, etc.\n - revise lu_object LRU, busy objects are not in LRU list any more\n - cleanup the code by defining cl_object_kill\n\nFuture work:\n - now pages and locks are holding a refcount against cl_object, this\n   causes cl_objects can't be purged by shrinker if there exists pages\n   and locks for an object. This is very bad, it needs fixing.\n - fairness of lu_object lru algorithm - lru is now tightly coupled with\n   hash, must fix.\n\nChange-Id: I6c2c6479709666e32a884524a48ce3351636c399\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jay@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
